<section id="resources" aria-label="Toolbox and external resources">
  <div class="wrap">
    <h2>Toolbox & External Resources</h2>
    <p class="lead">
      Different concerns may benefit from different therapeutic tools. Explore trusted external resources,
      worksheets, and practical supports by concern and age group. This page is educational only and does
      not replace individualized clinical care.
    </p>

    <div class="card soft" style="margin-bottom:14px">
      <h3>Before you use these resources</h3>
      <p>
        These links are meant to help you learn, reflect, and build language for what you may be experiencing.
        They are not a diagnosis, not a treatment plan, and not a substitute for professional care.
        Some tools are best used with a clinician, especially when symptoms are severe, trauma-related,
        safety-sensitive, or significantly affecting daily functioning.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="card" style="margin-bottom:14px">
      <h3 style="margin-bottom:10px">Find a resource</h3>
      <p style="margin-bottom:12px; color:var(--muted)">
        Search by concern, keyword, age group, or type of support. Examples: <b>ADHD</b>, <b>worksheet</b>, <b>teen</b>, <b>panic</b>, <b>parents</b>.
      </p>

      <input
        id="toolboxSearch"
        type="search"
        placeholder="Search ADHD, depression, worksheet, teen, trauma..."
        aria-label="Search toolbox resources"
        style="width:100%; padding:14px 16px; border:1px solid var(--line); border-radius:14px; font:inherit; color:var(--text); background:#fff; outline:none;"
      />

      <div style="margin-top:14px">
        <div style="font-size:13px; color:var(--muted); margin-bottom:8px">Filter by concern</div>
        <div class="chips" id="toolboxConcernFilters">
          <button class="chip toolbox-chip active" type="button" data-concern="all">All</button>
          <button class="chip toolbox-chip" type="button" data-concern="depression">Depression</button>
          <button class="chip toolbox-chip" type="button" data-concern="anxiety">Anxiety</button>
          <button class="chip toolbox-chip" type="button" data-concern="adhd">ADHD</button>
          <button class="chip toolbox-chip" type="button" data-concern="trauma">Trauma / PTSD</button>
          <button class="chip toolbox-chip" type="button" data-concern="ocd">OCD</button>
          <button class="chip toolbox-chip" type="button" data-concern="selfesteem">Self-esteem</button>
          <button class="chip toolbox-chip" type="button" data-concern="children">Children</button>
          <button class="chip toolbox-chip" type="button" data-concern="teens">Teens</button>
          <button class="chip toolbox-chip" type="button" data-concern="parents">Parents</button>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div style="margin-top:14px">
        <div style="font-size:13px; color:var(--muted); margin-bottom:8px">Filter by age group</div>
        <div class="chips" id="toolboxAgeFilters">
          <button class="chip toolbox-agechip active" type="button" data-age="all">All ages</button>
          <button class="chip toolbox-agechip" type="button" data-age="children">Children</button>
          <button class="chip toolbox-agechip" type="button" data-age="teens">Teens</button>
          <button class="chip toolbox-agechip" type="button" data-age="adults">Adults</button>
          <button class="chip toolbox-agechip" type="button" data-age="parents">Parents / Caregivers</button>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div id="toolboxResultCount" class="fine" style="margin-top:10px">Showing all resources.</div>
    </div>

    <div class="grid2" id="toolboxGrid">

      <div class="card toolbox-item"
           data-concern="depression"
           data-age="teens adults"
           data-keywords="depression mdd low mood sadness hopelessness worksheet workbook behavioral activation routine thought tracking self compassion nimh cci">
        <h3>MDD / Depression</h3>
        <p>
          Helpful when low mood, loss of interest, hopelessness, guilt, withdrawal,
          or reduced daily functioning are getting in the way.
        </p>

        <div class="badgeRow">
          <span class="badge">Behavioral activation</span>
          <span class="badge">Thought tracking</span>
          <span class="badge">Routine rebuilding</span>
          <span class="badge">Worksheets</span>
        </div>

        <div class="resourceList">
          <a class="resource" href="https://www.nimh.nih.gov/health/publications/depression" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
            <div class="rIcon" aria-hidden="true">D</div>
            <div class="rMain">
              <b>NIMH: Depression</b>
              <span>Trusted overview of symptoms, treatment options, and finding help.</span>
            </div>
            <div class="rLink">Open →</div>
          </a>

          <a class="resource" href="https://www.cci.health.wa.gov.au/resources/looking-after-yourself/depression" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
            <div class="rIcon" aria-hidden="true">W</div>
            <div class="rMain">
              <b>CCI: Depression Self-Help Resources</b>
              <span>Free modules, worksheets, and exercises for low mood and negative thinking.</span>
            </div>
            <div class="rLink">Open →</div>
          </a>
        </div>

        <details>
          <summary>What may be useful here?</summary>
          <p>
            Start with the overview first, then use worksheets for activity scheduling,
            mood tracking, and small-step reactivation.
          </p>
        </details>
      </div>

